  Wincer: It's the worst thing
        I've ever seen.

03:10.357 --> 03:14.826
 There's a legend around here,
that a farmer killed his family.

04:01.642 --> 04:08.046
    Morgan: If you mess with
  Rayborn's daughter, you mess
      with the pitchfork.

04:12.786 --> 04:15.554
  This is right outside of out
           perimeter.

04:15.556 --> 04:16.988
Does anybody live out this way?

04:16.991 --> 04:17.889
       I don't think so.

04:23.230 --> 04:26.164
            (Cheers)

04:37.211 --> 04:38.844
       (Chainsaw engine)

04:39.747 --> 04:44.650
           (Screams)

04:58.265 --> 05:00.132
         Run! Run! Run!

05:14.248 --> 05:15.414
            No! No!

05:15.949 --> 05:17.382
        (Scream in pain)

06:23.550 --> 06:25.550
     Who the hell is that?

06:29.056 --> 06:31.022
      I know who that is.

06:52.813 --> 06:54.579
             Sorry.

07:23.744 --> 07:26.745
        (Radio chatter)

07:39.393 --> 07:41.259
   This shit doesn't happen.

07:43.597 --> 07:50.569
  I mean we caught the fucking
    Boogie Man, or Dracula,
  or hell, the devil himself.

07:50.571 --> 07:54.673
You understand what I'm saying?
 - Yeah, you guys grow 'em big,
   and you grow 'em crazy...

07:54.675 --> 07:55.640
      I'll give you that.

07:55.642 --> 07:58.176
   Nah, it's more than that.

08:00.614 --> 08:04.115
 Did you ever play that Bloody
 Mary game when you were kids?

08:04.651 --> 08:06.985
 What where you stare into the
    mirror and say her name?

08:07.554 --> 08:08.353
             Yeah.

08:08.722 --> 08:09.621
          Yeah, sure.

08:10.757 --> 08:13.191
 Did she ever come to life and
    start murdering people?

08:15.829 --> 08:18.497
      I'm not trying to be
     insensitive, I'm not.

08:18.499 --> 08:19.798
       It's just that...

08:21.869 --> 08:23.568
when we was kids, growing up...

08:24.137 --> 08:26.505
       He's the reason we
    didn't playin the woods.

08:27.708 --> 08:30.075
       Those stories you
       tell each other...

08:30.077 --> 08:32.644
  trying to keep each other up
    late at night at camp...

08:32.645 --> 08:35.380
        were about him.
     - When you were a kid?

08:35.381 --> 08:39.217
             Yeah.
  - Dang. That dude looks good
      for like, a hundred.

08:39.219 --> 08:40.619
              Ha!

08:41.655 --> 08:44.121
 I might have been a teenager,
     but you get my point.

08:44.558 --> 08:46.558
  Why were you still going to
      camp as a teenager?

08:46.960 --> 08:49.694
 It was vacation bible school.

08:50.797 --> 08:52.831
       That's not weird!

08:59.373 --> 09:03.375
    You know I saw him once,
      or I thought I did.

09:05.412 --> 09:08.713
      We were working late
       on Christmas Eve.

09:09.283 --> 09:12.584
     Car wreck, completely
      engulfed in flames.

09:12.719 --> 09:14.586
      Couple lost control.

09:15.856 --> 09:18.323
    Well it just felt weird.

09:19.860 --> 09:22.694
   I don't know if it was the
      wind or the cold...

09:22.696 --> 09:25.730
  or it was Christmas Eve and
I just didn't want to be there.

09:33.006 --> 09:35.507
    (On Radio): Hey Wincer,
         what you got?

09:39.079 --> 09:41.112
     I didn't really think
        about it then...

09:41.114 --> 09:43.848
      but on the way home,
       from the scene...

09:43.850 --> 09:47.619
       I passed right by
     the old Rayborn place.

09:48.855 --> 09:51.656
 Well, I wouldn't have admitted
   then, but I'll tell you...

09:51.658 --> 09:53.959
  scared the shit out of me...

09:53.961 --> 09:56.394
    that some fucking crazy,
           old hermit

09:56.396 --> 10:00.398
would've been that close to me,
    in the dark, at night...

10:00.934 --> 10:03.168
   well, it'd scare anybody.

10:04.371 --> 10:06.304
   Was Rayborn his real name?

10:06.740 --> 10:08.773
             Yeah.

10:09.710 --> 10:12.711
 'Til they started calling him
           Pitchfork.

10:20.754 --> 10:23.088
Hey, if they can keep him alive,
  you're gonna need to put...

10:23.090 --> 10:25.056
 ...a small army on his floor.

10:25.058 --> 10:26.658
         Yeah, no shit.

10:26.660 --> 10:28.627
Yeah, media's gonna be a bitch.

10:28.996 --> 10:30.629
      I thought you meant
        if he wakes up.

10:32.132 --> 10:34.232
  I don't believe in monsters.

10:36.703 --> 10:38.003
             Fuck!

10:40.440 --> 10:43.208
          (Screaming)

10:49.883 --> 10:52.217
          (Screaming)

11:03.063 --> 11:05.930
           (Grunting)

11:36.363 --> 11:38.396
       Morgan: Let me ask
        you something...

11:38.398 --> 11:40.865
     what do you think the
   chances are that Steven...

11:40.867 --> 11:43.368
      would come work with
     us down on the boats?

11:43.370 --> 11:44.569
            (Laughs)

11:44.571 --> 11:46.571
   Well, let's see after you
        sold half our...

11:46.573 --> 11:48.573
      ...gear to send him
        off to college.

11:48.575 --> 11:50.608
Yeah. Does he have to know that?

11:53.747 --> 11:55.814
  Morgan: It's good to see you
   boys back together again.

11:57.084 --> 12:00.218
       You know I'd sell
     everything I own if...

12:00.220 --> 12:02.220
     I thought there was a
       chance in hell...

12:02.222 --> 12:04.689
   you'd wise up and get the
       hell out of here.

12:04.691 --> 12:07.192
     Bring it on, alright.
         Alright buddy.

12:12.232 --> 12:16.935
  (Whispering) They said like
  25 dead, including his dad.

12:16.937 --> 12:19.838
  Oh my God. That's terrible.

12:21.141 --> 12:23.108
       Make sure you give
     that to Dr. Shapiro...

12:23.110 --> 12:26.010
      he needs it as soon
      as you can. Thanks.

12:31.184 --> 12:35.787
      (Paramedic coughing)

12:45.532 --> 12:48.900
           (Coughing)

14:04.010 --> 14:07.111
             (Sobs)

14:29.502 --> 14:32.337
  Steven hasn't come out yet?

14:33.106 --> 14:35.039
            Not yet.

14:36.343 --> 14:38.676
         He'll be fine.

14:40.780 --> 14:45.083
  We use to play pretty rough
    when we were kids, so...

14:45.085 --> 14:47.719
          he knows how
       to take a beating.

14:51.224 --> 14:52.657
            (Laughs)

14:54.828 --> 14:59.898
     I saw him tear up from
        a splinter once.

15:02.168 --> 15:09.908
