15:10.143 --> 15:12.911
    Tiburon: It's called the
       Day of the Dead...

15:12.913 --> 15:17.315
    (Speaking spanish), it's
     a time to remember...

15:17.317 --> 15:19.350
 those that we've lost, and...

15:19.486 --> 15:21.853
     the ones who have gone
         on before us.

15:22.188 --> 15:23.521
    I've seen that on TV and
             stuff

15:23.523 --> 15:25.823
 it's like a scary Mardi Gras,
             right?

15:28.261 --> 15:31.963
       Yeah, pretty much.

15:35.669 --> 15:36.868
            (Laughs)

15:36.870 --> 15:38.503
      They didn't let you
       have the day off?

15:39.673 --> 15:41.172
         I did not ask.

15:41.374 --> 15:44.742
     Man, if I was Mexican,
  I wouldn't be working zombie
          Mardi Gras.

15:47.047 --> 15:49.047
You know, that is disrespectful.

15:49.049 --> 15:55.453
It's a celebration of a passing
 soul and to remind us that...

15:55.455 --> 16:00.858
   life is just a dream, and
     death is when we wake.

16:02.395 --> 16:04.195
       That's beautiful.

16:06.433 --> 16:08.599
           Thank you.

16:08.802 --> 16:11.736
   But, you have parades and
     throw candy too right?

16:11.738 --> 16:13.438
       That's Mardi Gras.

16:14.107 --> 16:15.440
        Woah woah, hey!

16:16.242 --> 16:17.241
             Yeah?

16:17.243 --> 16:18.309
        Where ya headed?

16:18.478 --> 16:20.311
    Second floor, what's up?

16:20.313 --> 16:21.612
         Is it urgent?

16:21.614 --> 16:23.881
       Man, I'm at work!

16:23.883 --> 16:27.952
      You got a minute to
        conference call?

16:28.288 --> 16:30.455
 Didn't your ass just go smoke?

16:30.457 --> 16:32.757
        Maybe, slow day.

16:33.693 --> 16:36.828
You know, one of these days they
  gon' catch on to the fact...

16:36.830 --> 16:39.130
    that you don't do shit!

16:39.132 --> 16:42.133
            (Laughs)
      Yeah. Maybe, maybe.

16:42.135 --> 16:46.371
Alright man, you twisted my arm.
    Yo Tiburon, you coming?

16:46.373 --> 16:50.008
    Oh no, I get to get back
      to these checklists.

16:50.010 --> 16:52.643
      Alright well, don't
      work too hard, man.

16:53.046 --> 16:55.079
         He won't, it's
      mexican Mardi Gras.

16:55.382 --> 16:57.382
            No shit?
       - I shit you not.

16:58.184 --> 16:59.384
            Gringos.

17:04.891 --> 17:05.957
           (Laughing)

17:06.159 --> 17:07.925
   Mardi Gras, Cinco de Mayo,
      they got everything.

17:08.194 --> 17:10.228
   Hey man look, who was that
    they brought in earlier?

17:11.263 --> 17:12.896
    I don't know. They came
      in through the back.

17:13.333 --> 17:14.866
       Through the morgue
        entrance right?

17:14.867 --> 17:15.532
             Yeah.

17:15.535 --> 17:16.567
              Why?

17:16.569 --> 17:18.435
         I don't know.

17:18.438 --> 17:21.239
  They did that shit that last
 time the mayor got his DUI...

17:21.407 --> 17:23.241
         snuck his ass
      through the back...

17:23.242 --> 17:25.343
    like I wasn't suppose to
       know who he is...

17:25.345 --> 17:27.244
      shit, I know who the
      fuck he is. Ah Shit!

17:27.247 --> 17:28.179
             What?

17:28.181 --> 17:29.280
 Man, I gotta go back to the...

17:29.282 --> 17:30.615
   break room, get my smokes.

17:30.617 --> 17:32.116
    I'll bum you one, c'mon.

17:32.118 --> 17:36.254
          Hell no man!
         You smoke that
      nasty menthol crap.

17:36.256 --> 17:38.623
              So?
             - So?!

17:38.625 --> 17:42.493
Dude that's full of fiberglass.
        That shit's way
       worse for you man.

17:42.495 --> 17:46.564
    Oh. So it's more deadly
       than just smoking?
             Idiot.

18:03.183 --> 18:04.682
          (Door Slams)
            (Grunts)

18:07.020 --> 18:10.855
       (Noise continues)

18:32.612 --> 18:33.778
             Shit.

18:40.887 --> 18:42.120
         (Violent thud)

19:01.641 --> 19:03.708
           Oh, sorry.
          - It's okay.

19:10.116 --> 19:11.382
           You okay?

19:13.987 --> 19:16.087
      Said might have some
        nerve damage...

19:16.856 --> 19:17.889
      physical therapy...

19:18.658 --> 19:23.694
          It'll be ok.
        Baby, baby, it's
         fine, really.

19:23.696 --> 19:26.063
        Said it could've
        been alot worse.

19:26.866 --> 19:29.267
       Has anyone checked
          you out yet?

19:29.702 --> 19:31.836
          Not really.

19:32.772 --> 19:35.506
       They want to check
      for a heartbeat, so.

19:36.576 --> 19:38.242
   Did they do your CAT scan?

19:38.244 --> 19:40.144
          No, not yet.

19:40.380 --> 19:42.246
        Checking you for
        "dain bramage?"

19:42.248 --> 19:45.316
            (Laughs)
      New "dain bramage."

19:47.320 --> 19:49.987
     Have you..had a chance
     to talk to anyone yet?

19:51.191 --> 19:52.924
         No, I gotta...

19:53.693 --> 19:56.160
          go down and
      identify the... umm.

20:04.971 --> 20:07.872
            Amanda?

20:12.812 --> 20:15.146
  They towed that truck out of
    here about an hour ago.

20:15.949 --> 20:17.682
 You know a bunch of kids head
  out here for some thrills...

20:17.684 --> 20:19.717
       and end up in this
    crazy fucking nightmare.

20:20.620 --> 20:24.488
 Whole thing turns my stomach.
      - You see that poor
     bastard in the woods?

20:24.490 --> 20:26.390
        With the fucking
       thing on his face?
            - Yeah.

20:26.392 --> 20:28.659
       Yeah, I saw it...

20:28.661 --> 20:30.695
  I don't fucking believe it.

20:31.297 --> 20:32.230
       I mean honestly...

20:32.532 --> 20:34.131
       have you ever seen
      anything like this?

20:36.236 --> 20:39.303
     Man, there ain't ever
    been anything like this.

20:44.177 --> 20:45.343
          Lt. Dayton?

20:46.679 --> 20:47.578
             Yeah?

20:47.580 --> 20:51.749
    The city guys posted at
       the hospital said
 the ambulance isn't there yet.

20:51.751 --> 20:54.652
You sure? They told everyone to
  else use the back entrance.

20:54.654 --> 20:56.721
        He said they're
      covering both sides.

20:57.323 --> 20:58.923
      They never made it.

21:01.961 --> 21:04.595
    Ole Wincer could fuck up
 a cup of coffee, couldn't he?

21:04.597 --> 21:06.664
  I'll tell you what, you tell
      them to stay put...

21:06.665 --> 21:08.732
   in case they radio in, you
     follow me up the nine,
 see if we can chase them down.

21:08.735 --> 21:10.735
     'Til we locate Wincer
    everyone reports to me.

21:41.267 --> 21:43.934
       Wasn't sure if you
     were a coffee drinker.

21:44.437 --> 21:45.736
      Only if it's Irish.

21:47.607 --> 21:49.206
            Thanks.

21:56.616 --> 21:57.515
          You know...

21:58.451 --> 22:00.885
  I remember you from school.

22:01.921 --> 22:03.120
           Fairhope?

22:05.325 --> 22:08.059
          Go Pirates.

22:10.763 --> 22:13.531
 Yeah, you were a couple grades
     ahead of me, but I...

22:13.966 --> 22:15.499
        I saw you in the
        halls and stuff.

22:15.935 --> 22:17.568
  You were in Steven's grade.

22:17.570 --> 22:18.469
             Yeah.

22:21.307 --> 22:24.275
      I didn't know him or
      anything, I just...

22:25.878 --> 22:28.145
    Small school, you know?

22:28.581 --> 22:31.215
          Yeah, tiny.

22:35.254 --> 22:38.155
   You...you left before the
   year was over, didn't you?

22:43.563 --> 22:45.596
  I'm not a stalker I promise,
              I...

22:46.099 --> 22:47.598
          I just, uh.

22:47.600 --> 22:52.737
  Yeah, I dropped out to help
      my dad on his boat.

22:52.739 --> 22:54.805
       He was gonna lose
        it to the bank.

22:58.511 --> 23:00.177
           I never...

23:04.384 --> 23:05.316
             So...

23:06.119 --> 23:09.353
     your dad, I mean he...

23:11.391 --> 23:13.190
             Yeah.

23:17.296 --> 23:18.796
              I...

23:19.899 --> 23:21.632
          I wasn't...

23:24.036 --> 23:25.936
           I'm sorry.

23:28.374 --> 23:30.441
      I wasn't even there.

23:34.714 --> 23:37.047
 Do you want to talk about it?

23:39.786 --> 23:41.318
      I just want answers.

23:42.555 --> 23:46.090
   The police are telling us
     two different things.

23:47.126 --> 23:49.593
   It doesn't make any sense.

23:56.369 --> 23:58.369
          You know...

23:58.671 --> 24:01.105
      I've been here for a
      couple of years now.

24:02.575 --> 24:06.277
     And I've seen alot of
   people dealing with loss.

24:06.679 --> 24:07.978
             But...

24:09.615 --> 24:11.816
    nothing quite like this.

24:14.654 --> 24:17.621
 Whenever there's a tragedy...

24:20.993 --> 24:25.830
      It's always so hard
       on the survivors.

24:28.768 --> 24:31.335
        And I don't just
       mean the families.

24:32.972 --> 24:35.239
       I mean the people
      who were involved...

24:36.976 --> 24:40.010
      who could've just as
      easily not made it.

24:46.118 --> 24:52.189
   Not only do you have this
     pain and loss, but...

24:54.360 --> 24:57.795
      but you can get a...

24:57.797 --> 25:00.598
   guilt that comes with it.

25:05.505 --> 25:08.272
  Sometimes it's hard to find.

25:27.593 --> 25:30.261
  It's hard to be a survivor.

25:34.367 --> 25:37.835
    It starts to feel easier
       just to give up...

25:40.940 --> 25:43.741
    but you can't, you know?

25:45.511 --> 25:48.779
Mary: You have to keep fighting.

25:50.316 --> 25:52.383
     (Heartbeat on monitor)
          There it is.

25:59.358 --> 26:01.859
   Sounds really strong too.

26:02.962 --> 26:05.029
  I'll give you two a minute.

26:11.771 --> 26:14.138
 I don't mean to be intrusive.

26:14.473 --> 26:17.541
   No, my dad would have told
     me to suck it up too.

26:19.111 --> 26:23.147
    That's not exactly what
         I was saying.

26:23.149 --> 26:24.782
            I know.

26:24.984 --> 26:26.784
         (Phone rings)

26:29.188 --> 26:31.555
    I have to deal with the
 families that come in here...

26:31.557 --> 26:33.591
      all the time and...

26:35.061 --> 26:37.428
    it's never easy for the
       one that made it.

26:41.467 --> 26:45.135
   (Phone ringing continues)

26:45.137 --> 26:48.272
     If you need anyone to
     talk to or anything...

26:48.474 --> 26:51.642
        I work until 10.

26:55.514 --> 26:57.314
            Thanks.

26:59.251 --> 27:01.352
   (Phone ringing continues)

27:13.766 --> 27:17.501
        Hi, front desk.

27:18.971 --> 27:21.505
     Down in the archives?

27:22.174 --> 27:24.942
      Ok, sure, what file?

27:26.178 --> 27:29.346
     Ok, yeah it'll just be
      a couple of minutes.

27:31.484 --> 27:34.051
   On TV: Hey boys and girls,
      it's Captain Morgan.

27:34.053 --> 27:35.853
  And you know what, it's that
      time of year for...

27:35.855 --> 27:38.922
        Captain Morgan's
        Haunted Hayride.

27:39.692 --> 27:41.425
 We got werewolves, we got ...

27:41.427 --> 27:43.427
    zombies, we got headless
     people running all...

27:43.429 --> 27:44.695
         we got it all!

27:44.830 --> 27:48.866
So, come on down Friday the 30th
    and Saturday the 31st...

27:48.868 --> 27:51.702
 that's Halloween night and if
     you're brave enough...

27:51.704 --> 27:55.005
     to ride in our ride of
     terror and survive...

27:55.007 --> 27:58.175
  well then you might just get
       to meet Pitchfork.

27:58.177 --> 28:00.044
      Pitchfork, himself!

28:01.514 --> 28:03.147
 Make sure you bring the kids!

28:03.149 --> 28:05.182
      (Laughs maniacally)

29:45.384 --> 29:47.751
            No! No!

29:50.890 --> 29:52.923
       (Screams in agony)

30:28.327 --> 30:29.293
          Feel better?

30:30.062 --> 30:31.862
          Not really.

30:32.097 --> 30:34.665
    I mean, about the baby,
       little Steven, Jr.

30:35.868 --> 30:37.234
         You mean Lily.

30:37.236 --> 30:39.236
             Lily?!

30:39.238 --> 30:40.804
   Yeah, you don't like Lily?

30:40.806 --> 30:42.472
        I really don't.

30:42.975 --> 30:45.242
       This is gonna be a
       problem isn't it?

30:45.244 --> 30:47.177
   I can almost guarantee it.

30:52.017 --> 30:54.484
 We're not naming our son Lily.

30:54.486 --> 30:56.386
          (Both laugh)

30:57.957 --> 31:01.491
     Sorry Mr. Summers, the
    doctor will see you now.

31:10.836 --> 31:12.903
           Love you.
        - Love you too.

31:44.136 --> 31:46.003
    (Metal door swings open)

36:33.458 --> 36:37.127
      (Screams) Oh my god!
        - Sorry, sorry.
   Oh, my god! You scared me.

36:37.129 --> 36:41.831
     Yeah...I thought I was
      going the wrong way.

36:41.833 --> 36:44.100
        Where ya headed?

36:44.101 --> 36:46.368
         Waiting room.
  - No, that's the right way.
 Everything just looks kinda...

36:46.371 --> 36:48.638
        messed up cause
      they're remodeling.

36:48.640 --> 36:52.709
  Tax dollars at work I guess.
   - Alright, thanks...sorry.

37:01.587 --> 37:02.452
        (Muffled shriek)

37:13.532 --> 37:14.564
           (Screams)

37:36.688 --> 37:37.821
              Hey!

37:37.956 --> 37:39.222
             Corey!

37:39.458 --> 37:41.224
       Hey, put her down!

37:41.927 --> 37:43.226
            Rayborn!

38:47.292 --> 38:49.192
Security Guard: Drop the knife!

38:50.228 --> 38:51.795
